Epigyne (
Fig. 9
). Lateral lobes distinct, nearly touching posteriorly; medially, epigynal plate with large depression, rounded anteriorly, undulate posteriorly; copulatory openings located laterally.

Vulva (
Fig. 10
). Medially projecting v-shaped area; large copulatory ducts extending posterolaterally to elongate spermathecae, directed anteriorly; a second, smaller pair of spermathecae located at the junction between the copulatory ducts and the larger pair of spermathecae; fertilisation ducts directed anterolaterally, small posterodorsal fold present.

Pedipalp. (
Figs 11–12
). Fm, spination d 0– 0–1 ; RTA with 2 apophyses, dorsal apophysis much longer than the ventral apophysis, long, narrow, curved ventrally, rounded at tip; ventral apophysis approximately a third of the length of dorsal apophysis, small, quadrate; two apophyses connected by thin keel; cymbium round to triangular; conductor large, pointed laterally, with finger-like process directed ventrally; embolus long and slender, arising from large tegular lobe, tapering abruptly, beginning at 7 o'clock, terminating at 1 o'clock; MA with wide base, with single process tapering to a pointed, hooked tip, directed anteriorly.

Distribution. Known only from the type locality (
Fig. 37
).
